Another pillar of this talk is technical tips and tricks that we learned working on a cross-generation game.

23
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:12,161
So there were a lot of things that we picked up along the way in terms of learnings when it comes to pushing next-gen visual effects,

24
00:01:12,161 --> 00:01:18,027
as well as working on a cross-generation title, working on something that had to be on both the PlayStation 4 and PlayStation 5.

25
00:01:18,927 --> 00:01:23,690
And the last theme was something that kind of evolved as I was working on this talk.

26
00:01:23,690 --> 00:01:26,671
And that one is really pushing forward through the unknown,

27
00:01:26,671 --> 00:01:29,333
taking risks and working together to create something new and great.

28
00:01:29,333 --> 00:01:35,316
There were a number of effects that, you know, when we were starting to work on this game,

29
00:01:35,316 --> 00:01:37,377
we weren't entirely sure how we were going to pull them off.

30
00:01:38,237 --> 00:01:43,682
And I really feel like we learned a lot by taking a risk, by challenging ourselves, and

31
00:01:43,682 --> 00:01:46,284
by pushing forward through the unknown.

32
00:01:46,284 --> 00:01:49,306
And it was really wonderful to be able to work on that.

33
00:01:50,522 --> 00:01:53,205
So I'm going to give you a quick overview of this talk.

34
00:01:53,205 --> 00:01:56,808
During our time together, we're going to be talking about Miles's powers.

35
00:01:56,808 --> 00:02:02,693
That includes his venom powers, so that's his bioelectricity that generates within himself.

36
00:02:02,693 --> 00:02:08,357
That's also his camouflage ability, so his camouflage is when he turns invisible.

37
00:02:08,357 --> 00:02:09,879
We're also going to touch on creating spectacle.

38
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:14,122
So spectacle is a really important part of this game,

